== Improvement List ==
(Code audit findings — polish before adding new features)


--- Phase 1: Critical Bug-Risk Fixes ---

[DONE] 1. Fix silent error swallowing
      Added console.warn() to 10+ silent .catch(() => {}) and bare catch blocks.
      Errors in IDB writes, audio playback, data migration, and boot now log context.

[DONE] 2. Cap undo/redo stack size
      All 3 undo/redo systems (editor, skin editor, sculpt editor) now capped at MAX_UNDO=80.
      Oldest entries evicted when limit exceeded.

[DONE] 3. Prevent autosave race conditions
      _idbSet() now uses per-key write queues. Concurrent writes to the same IDB key
      are serialized automatically, eliminating data corruption risk.

[DONE] 4. Add deserialization validation
      deserializeObject() now validates position (3 numbers), quaternion (4 numbers),
      and scale (3 numbers, no zeros) before creating meshes. Invalid data logged and skipped.


--- Phase 2: Code Quality & Maintainability ---

[DONE] 5. Centralize magic numbers
      Named GHOST_OPACITY constant. Most other constants were already named individually
      (SUN_DISTANCE, PLAYER_RADIUS, etc.) — no further extraction needed.

[DONE] 6. Use string enums for modes/types
      Added MODES = { PLACE, SELECT, DELETE, PAINT, ERASE } and
      TRANSFORMS = { TRANSLATE, ROTATE, SCALE } constants. State initialized from enums.

[SKIP] 7. Consolidate duplicated clamping/normalization
      On inspection, existing clamp functions already follow a consistent pattern.
      Not worth abstracting further — each has distinct defaults and ranges.

[ ] 8. Clean up HTML-in-JS inline styles
      Skeleton editor, voxel editor, and sculpt editor embed large HTML strings
      with hardcoded inline styles. Extract repeated style patterns to CSS classes
      in index.html.
      Locations: main.js lines ~2117, 3489, 4718


--- Phase 3: UX & Robustness ---

[DONE] 9. Add confirmation dialogs for destructive actions
      clearAll() now prompts "Clear all N object(s) from the scene?" before proceeding.
      (Delete-single-object left without confirm since it's undoable.)

[DONE] 10. Keyboard shortcuts help overlay
       Press "?" to toggle a styled overlay showing all editor and playtest shortcuts.
       Click outside or press "?" again to dismiss.

[DONE] 11. Improve ghost object visibility
       Ghost placement now includes a blue wireframe overlay (0x58a6ff, opacity 0.5)
       in addition to the semi-transparent fill. Wireframe properly disposed on removal.

[DONE] 12. Better export error feedback
       All 4 export error handlers now include the actual error message in the alert.


--- Phase 4: QA & Test Hardening ---

[ ] 13. Convert diagnostic tests to real assertions
       Only smoke-runtime-export.js uses proper Node assert.
       The other 8 test files use console.log() with emoji and need manual verification.
       Convert to assert with meaningful messages and proper exit codes.

[ ] 14. Remove redundant test files
       test-movement-debug.js and test-movement-hud.js are fully superseded
       by test-playtest-movement.js. Archive or delete.

[ ] 15. Standardize test port
       test-tab-click.js uses port 8765, all others use 8000.
       Unify to a single configurable BASE_URL.

[ ] 16. Fix .last-run.json inconsistency
       Shows status:"failed" with empty failedTests array — contradictory.


--- Phase 5: Performance Quick Wins ---

[DONE] 17. Cache procedural textures
       _generatePatternCanvas() now caches canvases by pattern+color+scale key.
       Repeated calls for the same pattern return cached canvas instantly.

[DONE] 18. Throttle raycasting in coordinate HUD
       updateCoordHud() raycast now throttled to every 150ms.
       Position text still updates every frame; only the expensive aim-raycast is throttled.